headline: Did KeyCorp’s Expected C$81 Million Boost Just Shift Bank of Nova Scotia's (TSX:BNS) Investment Narrative?
summary: Earlier in January, Scotiabank said it expects its ownership stake in U.S. regional lender KeyCorp to contribute about C$81 million in reported net income, or roughly C$89 million on an adjusted basis, to its fiscal Q1 2026 results to be released on February 24, 2026. This anticipated lift from KeyCorp underscores how Scotiabank’s shift toward North American banking and tighter operations is increasingly influencing its overall earnings mix and capital-return capacity.
